                    "company": "IDH ",
                    "description": "In February 2014, IDH and partners launched the 'Sustainable Land and Water Program' (SLWP), funded by the Dutch ministry of Foreign Affairs. I was asked to lead this new program as Interim Director in its inception year. Since 2015 the landscapes work of IDH has evolved and grown under the leadership of Global Landscapes Director Daan Wensing.\n\nIn 2014, we identified several landscapes that were all sourcing areas for one or more commodities, and were presented with major environmental and/or social challenges. IDH worked with local stakeholders towards sustainable management of these landscapes, aiming for each stakeholder to see beyond their own land borders, beyond their own sector and interests, at the shared interests in the bigger landscape picture. Fascinating work. \n\nFor more information about IDH's current work on landscapes see https://www.idhsustainabletrade.com/landscapes/",
